# run github script Sophia-Script-for-Windows
#############################################

- open the terminal and set the default profile to "Windows PowerShell"
- download the script with the command...
  - irm script.sophi.app -useb | iex
- right click the windows icon and click "Windows Terminal (Admin)"
- change the current location to the sophia folder with the command...
  - cd [path to sophia folder]
- set execution policy to be able to run scripts only in the current powershell session with the command...
  - Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force
- run the sript with the command...
  - .\Sophia.ps1
- accept all defaults and uninstall everything





# install software from winget
##############################

# run the following command with "Command Prompt"...
winget install Bitwarden.Bitwarden && winget install eloston.ungoogled-chromium && winget install Discord.Discord && winget install rcmaehl.MSEdgeRedirect && winget install EpicGames.EpicGamesLauncher && winget install flux.flux && winget install GnuPG.GnuPG && winget install CPUID.HWMonitor && winget install Jackett.Jackett && winget install Joplin.Joplin && winget install LibreWolf.LibreWolf && winget install NordVPN.NordVPN && winget install qBittorrent.qBittorrent && winget install Valve.Steam && winget install TorProject.TorBrowser && winget install Ubisoft.Connect && winget install VideoLan.VLC





# install software from the internet
####################################

- AMD Website -> Drivers & Support -> Auto-Detect
- ventoy from github





# config
########
       
  # amd software
    - set graphics profile to "gaming" but enable "Radeon Enhanced Sync"


  # flux
    - set to "Color Fidelity"
  
  
  # qBittorrent
    - in preferences, configure power management, enable anonymous mode, and recheck torrents on completion
    - "View" tab -> Search Engine
    - configure search by...
        - jackett was already installed through winget, but you need to launch it to enable it
        - to install the plugin and configure jackett, open qbittorrent and open the "Search" tab -> search plugins -> click on the link -> click on "How to configure Jackett plugin"
        - open the plugin and copy the url, then open qbittorrent and open the "Search" tab -> search plugins -> install a new one -> Web link -> paste the plugin url
        - configure jackett by reading the rest of the github page
        
        
  # windows
    - if dual booting with another os, you need to configure windows to use UTC time, this is so the clock stays correct when switching between os's
      - you can do this by running the following command from an admin command prompt...
        - reg add "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\TimeZoneInformation" /v RealTimeIsUniversal /d 1 /t REG_DWORD /f
    - in file explorer, pin the path "C:\ProgramData\Microsoft\Windows\Start Menu\Programs" to Quick access
    


